Set a timer to show spinner after 1 sec. 

If the request is completed &lt; 1s you will never see it else it will be hidden if it is shown.

```
timer: number;
intercept(req: HttpRequest&lt;any&gt;, next: HttpHandler): Observable&lt;HttpEvent&lt;any&gt;&gt; {
  if(this.timer){
    cancelTimeout(this.timer);
  }
  this.timer = setTimeout(() =&gt; this.spinner.show(), 1000);

  return next.handle(req).pipe(finalize(() =&gt; {
    this.spinner.hide();
    if(this.timer){
      cancelTimeout(this.timer);
    }
  }));
}
```

You can use `combineLatest` + `timer`.

If the response is less than 1s, it will wait for the timer to end. The opposite will follow the actual response time

```ts
  intercept(req: HttpRequest&lt;any&gt;, next: HttpHandler): Observable&lt;HttpEvent&lt;any&gt;&gt; {
    this.spinner.show();
    return combineLatest(timer(1000), next.handle(req))
           .pipe(finalize(() =&gt; this.spinner.hide()));
  }
```

